-- Brazilian Stock Movers: ALL, Cosan, HRT, OGX Petroleo
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-02-22T17:49:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-22/brazilian-stock-movers-all-cosan-hrt-ogx-petroleo.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 3:45 p.m. local time. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index fell 0.4 percent to 65,918.77.  ALL America Latina Logistica SA (ALLL3)  (ALLL3 BS) gained 2.4
percent to 11.29 reais, headed for a seven-month high.  Cosan SA
Industria & Comercio (CSAN3)  agreed to pay 896.5 million reais ($524.7
million) for a stake in ALL,  Latin America ’s largest railroad
company.  Cosan (CSAN3)  (CSAN3 BS), which controls the world’s largest sugar
port terminal, fell 5.2 percent to 29.40 reais, the biggest
intraday drop in five months.  HRT Participacoes em Petroleo SA  (HRTP3 BS) gained 8
percent to 613 reais. HRT, an oil explorer, jumped after partner
 Energulf Resources Inc. (ENG)  said it has 3.2 billion barrels of
recoverable oil in an area of  Namibia .  OGX Petroleo & Gas Participacoes SA (OGXP3)  (OGXP3 BS) gained 2.3
percent to 18.05 reais, the highest intraday price in 10 months.
Crude oil for April delivery rose as high as $106.47 a barrel on
the  New York Mercantile Exchange , the highest since May 5.  To contact the reporter on this story:
